  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Is chaga safe to take daily?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Chaga has been consumed as a tea and supplement for centuries in northern cultures with a strong safety record. No significant adverse effects have been reported in clinical or observational studies at standard supplementation doses (500 to 1,500mg of extract daily). However, chaga contains oxalates, which in very high doses could theoretically contribute to kidney stone formation in susceptible individuals. People with kidney disease or a history of oxalate kidney stones should consult their healthcare provider before supplementing chaga. Additionally, chaga may have blood-thinning properties and could interact with anticoagulant medications.' } },
