    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Chaga Gummies</h2>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What is chaga mushroom and what are its benefits?</summary><p>Chaga is a parasitic fungus growing on birch trees with the highest ORAC antioxidant score (146,700) of any natural substance. It contains beta-glucans for immune modulation, melanin for antioxidant protection, betulinic acid for anti-inflammatory effects, and exceptional SOD levels for cellular protection.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How does chaga support the immune system?</summary><p>Beta-glucan polysaccharides interact with immune cell receptors (Dectin-1, CR3) to modulate immune function. Unlike stimulants, beta-glucans balance immune responses — upregulating underactive and regulating overactive immunity.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What should I look for in a chaga gummy?</summary><p>Dual extraction (hot water + alcohol), verified beta-glucan content (minimum 20%), sclerotium or fruiting body source (not mycelium on grain), and third-party heavy metal testing.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Is chaga safe to take daily?</summary><p>Yes, with centuries of traditional use and no significant adverse effects at 500-1,500mg daily. Caution with kidney disease (oxalates), kidney stone history, and anticoagulant medications.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How long does it take for chaga to work?</summary><p>Immune modulation: 2-4 weeks. Antioxidant benefits: 4-8 weeks. Gut health: 2-3 weeks. Most experts recommend a minimum 60-day trial period.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What is the difference between chaga and other functional mushrooms?</summary><p>Chaga is the antioxidant champion (highest ORAC). Lion's mane targets cognition. Reishi targets stress/sleep. Cordyceps targets performance. Turkey tail has the strongest cancer research. Chaga uniquely combines antioxidants, betulinic acid, and immune beta-glucans.</p></details>

